    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=A used car due-diligence check has been run. Risk level: {{ $json.riskLevel }} (score: {{ $json.riskScore }}).\n\nVehicle: {{ $json.make }} {{ $json.model }}, first used {{ $json.firstUsedDate }}\nRegistration: {{ $json.registration }}\nTotal MOT tests: {{ $json.totalTests }}\nTotal failures: {{ $json.totalFails }}\nMileage-related red flags: {{ $json.mileageFlags.length > 0 ? $json.mileageFlags.join(', ') : 'None — mileage progression looks consistent' }}\nDangerous defects ever recorded: {{ $json.dangerousDefectCount }}\nCurrent recorded mileage: {{ $json.latestMileage }} miles\n\nFull MOT test history for reference: {{ JSON.stringify($json.rawMotTests) }}\n\nInstructions based on risk level:\n- If risk level is HIGH: open with a clear warning tone, strongly recommend an independent inspection before purchase, and be direct about the specific red flags.\n- If risk level is MEDIUM: note the concerns clearly but keep a balanced, informative tone — not alarming.\n- If risk level is LOW: reassure the reader this looks like a well-maintained vehicle, while still mentioning anything genuinely worth asking about.\n\nThen do the following:\n1. Search the web for common known problems, reliability issues, or recalls for this specific make, model, and approximate age.\n2. Write a plain-English risk assessment covering: overall condition, mileage trustworthiness, what the failure(s) indicate, and what to check/ask about when viewing in person.\n3. Include a \"known issues for this model\" section with real sources cited.\n4. Do not make definitive fraud claims — only flag patterns as \"worth asking about.\"",
        "options": {}
